import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="income", data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['income'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Income: {:.2f}'.format(data['income'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x="income", y="health", data=data, hue="region", palette="bright")
    plt.title("What is the relationship between income and life expectancy?", wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel="Income per Capita", ylabel="Life Expectancy")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='population', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['population'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['population'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.barplot(x="region", y="income", data=data, ci=None, color="b", ax=ax)
    sns.barplot(x="region", y="health", data=data, ci=None, color="r", ax=ax)
    ax.set_ylabel("Average Income and Life Expectancy")
    ax.set_xlabel("Region")
    ax.set_title("What is the average income and life expectancy in each region?")
    ax.legend(["Income", "Life Expectancy"])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
